[Review by saschagrunert]: Thanks for working on this! The root cause analysis is right (`isXfs` needs to run at test time), but the fix has a scoping issue, see inline comment. | [Review by saschagrunert]: /lgtm | [Inline on test/e2e_node/quota_lsci_test.go LNone]: This `BeforeEach` sets `useUnderLimit` at test runtime, but `diskConcealingPod(..., useUnderLimit, ...)` is called during Ginkgo tree construction (the body of `ginkgo.Context` runs eagerly to register child nodes). At that point `var useUnderLimit int` is still `0`, so the pod's Perl command bakes in `foreach (1..0)`, writing 0 bytes instead of 99/50 MB.

The test still passes because 0 bytes is trivially under the 100Mi limit (`evictionPriority: 0`), but it no longer validates the interesting case (near-limit usage not triggering a false eviction).

I'd suggest removing this block, restoring `useUnderLimit := 99` at the top of the function, and using `prePodCreationModificationFunc` on the under-limit pod spec instead. That callback runs in `runEvictionTest`'s `BeforeEach` right before pod creation (`eviction_test.go:779`), so `isXfs` evaluates at the right time:

```go
{
	evictionPriority: 0,
	pod: diskConcealingPod(fmt.Sprintf("emptydir-concealed-disk-under-sizelimit-quotas-%v", quotasRequested), useUnderLimit, &v1.VolumeSource{
		EmptyDir: &v1.EmptyDirVolumeSource{SizeLimit: &sizeLimit},
	}, v1.ResourceRequirements{}),
	prePodCreationModificationFunc: func(ctx context.Context, pod *v1.Pod) {
		if isXfs(framework.TestContext.KubeletRootDir) {
			pod.Spec.Containers[0].Command = []string{
				"perl",
				"-e",
				fmt.Sprintf(writeConcealedPodCommand, filepath.Join(volumeMountPath, "file"), 50 /* Mb */),
			}
		}
	},
},
```

This way the default (99 MB) is baked in at tree construction, and only the XFS case (50 MB) is applied at runtime. | [Inline on test/e2e_node/quota_lsci_test.go LNone]: Thanks, that's right. Fixed | [Inline on test/e2e_node/quota_lsci_test.go LNone]: nit: "below" no longer points anywhere meaningful now that the check moved into this closure.

```suggestion
					// XFS speculative preallocation can inflate apparent usage (see isXfs).
``` | [Inline on test/e2e_node/quota_lsci_test.go LNone]: Thanks, I have made the change.

