[Review by gemini-code-assist[bot]]: ## Code Review

This pull request introduces `TFLLMModel`, a Keras-compatible wrapper around HuggingFace causal language models, enabling fine-tuning with LoRA and text generation within the TensorFlow ecosystem. The review identified three critical issues: first, the fallback manual training loop fails when iterating over a `tf.data.Dataset` because it passes TensorFlow/NumPy tensors directly to PyTorch and can trigger a `TypeError` due to duplicate `labels` arguments; second, reloading a saved model from a local directory containing only LoRA adapters will fail unless the base model is loaded first and the adapters are applied via PEFT; and third, passing a Keras optimizer object to `compile()` will cause an `AttributeError` when calling `.lower()` on it.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> The [consumer version of Gemini Code Assist on GitHub](https://developers.google.com/gemini-code-assist/docs/review-repo-code) is being sunset. Starting **June 18, 2026**, new organization installations will be blocked, and all code review activity will officially cease on **July 17, 2026**.
> For more details on the timeline and next steps, please review the [Help Documentation](https://developers.google.com/gemini-code-assist/docs/deprecations/consumer-code-review). | [Inline on tensorflow/python/llm/llm_model.py L444]: ![high](https://www.gstatic.com/codereviewagent/high-priority.svg)

