[Inline on compiler/packages/babel-plugin-react-compiler/src/__tests__/fixtures/compiler/bug-inconsistent-memoization-object-mixed-properties.js L6]: This isn't correct

> Object mixing method shorthand and function expression properties **shouldn't** memoize entire object as a unit when deps change

```js
getValue() {
  return state;
}
```

should be treated as

```js
getValue: function() {
  return state;
}
``` | [Inline on compiler/packages/babel-plugin-react-compiler/src/__tests__/fixtures/compiler/bug-inconsistent-memoization-object-mixed-properties.js L6]: Good point — the test comment is wrong.

The correct direction is to make method shorthand (`getValue() {}`) behave like a function expression (`getValue: function() {}`), i.e. per-function memoization. I went the opposite way — pulling function expressions into the object scope — which is less optimal.

Will update the fix to go in the right direction: each function gets its own reactive scope regardless of syntax (shorthand vs expression). This is what #36153 attempted — just more surgical.

